  <refnamediv>
    <refname>im2uint16</refname>

    <refpurpose>Convert image to 16-bit unsigned integers</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>

    <synopsis>im2 = im2uint16(im)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>im</term>

        <listitem>
           An matrix/image, which can be ANY image supported by SIVP. 
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>im2</term>

        <listitem>
           Output image, a 16-bit unsigned integer matrix.
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>

  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para><literal>im2uint16</literal> convert intensity or RGB images to
    16-bit unsigned integers. If the input is of class
    <literal>uint16</literal>, the output image is identical to it. Otherwise,
    <literal>im2uint16</literal> rescales or offsets the data, and returns the
    equivalent image of class <literal>uint16</literal>.</para>
  </refsection>

